comments: Vucevic (CHI) absorbs the contact initiated by Dort (OKC) and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vucevic (CHI) firms up in Dort's (OKC) path and incidental contact occurs as Dort is moving through the pick.
Dort (OKC) allows DeRozan (CHI) to follow through after the release of the jump shot. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Pokusevski (OKC) slightly extends his arm into Caruso (CHI) as he is rolling toward the rim.
Pokusevski (OKC) and DeRozan (CHI) come together and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Dort (OKC) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Pokusevski (OKC) and Caruso (CHI) come together and marginal contact occurs during the rebound attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) places his hand on the ball and dislodges it from Williams (OKC).  Any further contact is incidental.

After Dort (OKC) comes away with the loose ball, OKC is granted a timeout and the timeout request is recognized before he passes the ball to Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC). Therefore, OKC is allowed to advance the ball when play resumes following the timeout.
Caruso (CHI) moves forwards into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) space and initiates leg to leg contact that causes him to lose his balance.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) places a hand on Caruso's (CHI) back with slight extension but the contact is marginal.
LaVine (CHI) initiates contact to Pokusevski's (OKC) arm that affects his control of the ball.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) reaches across DeRozan's (CHI) body and delivers contact to his arm during the driving shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) moves alongside Giddey's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) firms up in Dort's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Williams (CHI) does not give Dort (OKC) time and distance to avoid the pick and dislodges him from his legal guarding position as Dort is moving through the pick.
Dort (OKC) pulls the rim to an ?off-center' position, while the ball is in contact with the rim.
Dort (OKC) delivers contact to DeRozan's (CHI) arm during the shot attempt. On contact, DeRozan's shot attempt is affected.

Replay review of the foul called on DeRozan (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. DeRozan (CHI) jumps forward into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) space and initiates contact that affects his jump shot attempt.  Gilgeous-Alexander then makes contact with DeRozan's face as part of a normal shooting motion. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Dort (OKC) slightly extends his arms into Vucevic's (CHI) space as he is moving through the pick.
DeRozan's (CHI) legs slightly drift forward during his shot attempt and he avoids making contact with Dort (OKC).
Dosunmu (CHI) commits a take foul on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
Dort (OKC) moves alongside LaVine's (CHI) path and maintains a legal guarding position during the shot attempt.
